	PERFORMING ARTS      April 3 at Sisir Mancha; 6 pm: On the occasion of 150 years of Tagores birth anniversary, veteran artiste Enkashi Chattopadhyay presents a programme of solo Rabindrasangeet. Split in two halves, the first part will feature a selection of 15 songs from 56 lyrics that Tagore penned during 1910-1911. Of these, the first eight songs were included in Gitanjali. The next six songs are from Gitali. A selection of five songs from the play, Raja, is included in this half. The second half features Tagores interpretation of the universe and his place in the scheme of things. Hosted by Bhavna.     April 3 at Ankur Hall, P-5 Regent Estate; 5 pm: All India Music Festival presents its quarterly classical music fest. Featuring Krisnokali Datta (vocal), Bandana Chakravorty (vocal), Rampraparna Bhattacharjee (sitar), Jyotsna Ganguly (vocal) and Sandip Bhattacharjee (vocal).     April 3 at Rabindra Okakura Bhavan, Salt Lake; 6 pm: Unmesh presents Tabo Chhayataley, an evening of prose, poetry and audio-play based on Tagores work. Design amp; direction: Jagannath Basu.     April 4 at Rabindra Okakura Bhavan; 5 pm: Meena Art Gallerys 35th annual programme features solo recitals of Bengali songs and dance-drama Bal Gopal (dir: Purnima Choudhury).     April 4 at Jibanananda Sabhaghar; 6 pm: Chhandak presents an evening of songs, poems and audio-drama on the spring season.     April 4 at Kala Mandir; 6 pm: Sangit Kala Mandir presents an evening of devotional songs and classical vocal recital by Pandit Jasraj. Accompanying him will be Tripti Mukherjee (vocal support), Pandit Sohanlal Sharma (harmonium), Pandit S. Sekharan (mridangam) and Ustad Sabir Khan (tabla).     
